description: Physical fitness is a state of health and well-being and, more specifically, the ability to perform aspects of sports, occupations and daily activities.

The dumbbell is a type of exercise equipment used in weight training. Specifically, dumbbells are weights used without exercise machines. Dumbbells are sometimes also called hand weights and free weights
A form of high intensity interval training, CrossFit is a strength and conditioning workout that is made up of functional movement performed at a high intensity level.
A treadmill is a piece of exercise equipment that has a belt that loops around, driven by a motor. The continuous loop allows a person to walk or run on the treadmill in place.
“Strength does not come from physical capacity. It comes from an indomitable will.”
Exercise involves engaging in physical activity and increasing the heart rate beyond resting levels.
